description:
In collaboration with @iimunofficial, I‚Äôm delighted to launch their campaign aimed at first-time voters. 

India, the world‚Äôs largest democracy ‚Äî as we all wish it to remain! ‚Äî goes to elections starting next month. 

This election will be the largest electoral exercise ever conducted in the world. Citizens will cast their vote across 543 constituencies in 7 phases at over 10.5 lakh polling stations to elect the 18th Lok Sabha. This exercise will employ 1.5 crore polling officials and security staff, 55 lakh EVMs, and 4 lakh vehicles.

A total of 96.8 crore people have registered to vote. However, the most significant fact is that out of  these, 23 crore people between the age of 18-29 will be voting! I believe this is an election in which young people can truly determine the nation‚Äôs destiny.

I congratulate @iimunofficial on its #myfirstvote campaign and am happy to do my bit to amplify the need to vote!

- Dr. Shashi Tharoor

What the international community has allowed in Gaza will go down in history not only as a great shame for the whole of humanity, but as a turning point for the human race. 
Being blind to genocide as it is carried out with impunity, turning our backs to the merciless slaughter of thousands of innocent children, refusing to step in while an entire nation starves and begs for help, while hospitals are bombed, doctors tortured and humiliated, and patients allowed to die, enabling an oppressive regime by offering its ships our ports, fuelling its inhumane rampage by providing it with more and more funding and arms - all this has now set a horrendous precedent. 

All rules of justice, humanity and international decorum have been broken. Humanity has been bled, and each one of us will pay an unimaginable price for this some day unless we raise our voices and stand up for what is right today.üáµüá∏

description:
Today in Lok Sabha, I addressed critical concerns in the Motion of Thanks to the President's Address, spotlighting significant issues under the current Union Government. Highlighted the unmet promise of doubling farmers' income, with policy reversals like the ban on onion exports and ethanol production contributing to their plight. Called for extended accidental insurance for ASHA & Anganwadi workers and their spouses, reflecting the essential need for safeguarding our frontline workers.

The persistent social unrest in J&K and Manipur, alongside the mounting protests in Maharashtra over soaring fuel prices, the need for doctor protection, and demands for reservation, were brought to the forefront, urging immediate dialogue and action. Addressed the unfulfilled promises under EPS 95, affecting our seniors, and the cancellation of railway ticket concessions during COVID, which awaits reinstatement.

The alarming rate of unemployment and the shrinking availability of decent jobs for our youth, coupled with the inflation-driven increase in living costs for the middle class, were highlighted as pressing issues requiring urgent government intervention. Critiqued the inefficacy of the Ujjwala Yojana due to unaffordable LPG costs and proposed an expansion of Ayushman Bharat's ailment coverage to enhance healthcare accessibility.

Advocated for increasing train stops, like those of Garibrath, to benefit students, labourers, and the middle class, emphasizing the necessity of improving public transport accessibility. The implementable demand for reservation for the Maratha, Dhangar, Lingayat, and Muslim communities in Maharashtra was stressed, highlighting the critical role of political will in achieving social equity.

Concluded by urging the Centre to lead with empathy and compassion, calling for policies and governance that truly reflect the needs and aspirations of all Indians.

spoke during discussion on supplementary demand for grants and the appropriation bills 2023 in lok sabha today

questioned on the centre on why there is so much unemployment in the country hinjawadi  a proud example of the it sector in my constituency is facing a job crunch questioned the centre on its policies to address the same

on farmers centre is being consistently inconsistent in its policy  stressed the antifarmer policy of centre including the ban on onion export last week and imposition of 40 tax of farmers this has led to farmer unrest in maharashtra

on ethanol policy u turn on the sugar industry  while the commerce ministry promised to promote ethanol last week it changed its stance within 24 hours by banning production of ethanol from sugar

raised the issue of water pollution in my constituency in khadakwasala and how the centre has no standardisation of policy on climate and energy

questioned the centre that when indian banks can write off rs106 lakh crores for large corporations then why cant they write off farmer loans

on senior citizen pension  pointed to the contradictory stand of the government when pravash javdekar supported revision of pension in 2014 but hasnt increased it after being elected a sugar factory employee from daund who contributed rs500 every month for 33 years is receiving only rs1000 as pension

pointed to lack of policies for the social sector especially for asha anganwadis and  lack of funds for vayoshree yojana

urged the centre to not just focus on big infrastructure projects but also on policies for women pensioners farmers and those at the bottom of the pyramid

‚ÄúAn eye for an eye makes the whole world blind‚Äù ~ Mahatma Gandhi

I am shocked and ashamed that our country has abstained from voting for a ceasefire in Gaza.

 Our country was founded on the principles of non-violence and truth, principles for which our freedom fighters laid down their lives, these principles form the basis of the constitution that defines our nationhood. They represent the moral courage of India that guided its actions as a member of the international community.

To refuse to take a stand and watch in silence as every law of humanity is pulverised, food, water, medical supplies, communication and power is cut off to millions of people and thousands of men, women and children in Palestine are being annihilated goes against everything our country has stood for throughout its life as a nation.
